review_blob: Very good American dark lager.  Not too heavy and very drinkable.  Nice roasted taste.  A little thin tasting after awhile, but still good for a modestly priced widely available beer.

Very decent American dark lager.  Good roasted flavor, but not overpowering.  Decent color, not too heavy, and very drinkable.  If youre in south Minneapolis, check it out on tap at the Chatterbox Pub where its the house specialty known as the Chatterbox Lager...

The 2004 batch of Schells Hefeweizen was extraordinary.  The fruity character was bolstered by a banana-like taste which really puts this one on top.  No bitter aftertaste like a lot of Hefes.  Id take this one over any of the big European Hefes any day.

Decent brew from Schells.  Nice color and initial taste.  Grows a bit thin tasting, however, by the end of the bottle.  The less-expensive Schells Dark is actually a tad better for a dark-style American beer.

Best pumpkin flavored beer bar none.  Excellent spicy flavor; no moldy pumpkin taste like some other pumpkin beers have.  Orange color fits right in to the autumn theme of this exceptional brew.  Another Blue Moon winner...
beer_name: Blue Moon Harvest Moon Pumpkin Ale

review_blob: Excellent domestic witbier.  Fruity but not overwhelming.  No bitter aftertaste.  One of my favorite easy-to-find beers.
